.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-SCORE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-score \- Score tracked job resource efficiency
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose score [OPTIONS] [JOB_ID]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Compute a post\-run 0\-100 efficiency score for a tracked Slurm job from GPU sampler history, memory usage, active compute time, accounting, and best\-effort energy estimates.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to score.
.TP
\fB--sweep\fR \fIID\fR
Score every trial of this sweep id instead of a single job.
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--remote\fR \fIHOST\fR
Run this command on the login node's staged checkout from a prior `up \-\-remote`, over SSH, streaming output back. With no value, uses the configured login_host; accepts user@host (otherwise HPC_COMPOSE_REMOTE_USER / login_user / ~/.ssh/config).
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--pue\fR \fIFLOAT\fR
Power usage effectiveness multiplier for kWh estimates. Default: 1.2.
.TP
\fB--gpu\-tdp\-w\fR \fIWATTS\fR
Fallback GPU TDP in watts when sampler power is unavailable. Default: 300.
.TP
\fB--cpu\-watts\-per\-core\fR \fIWATTS\fR
Fallback CPU watts per allocated core for energy estimates. Default: 8.
.TP
\fB--sstat\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sstat executable. Default: sstat.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose score 12345
hpc\-compose score \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose score 12345 \-\-pue 1.3 \-\-gpu\-tdp\-w 350 \-\-format json
.fi
